    <article class = 'Claude Monet'>
        <h1>Monet's Life </h1>
        <p> Monet whilst most famous for a few collections was a prolific painter and really focused on transient light particularly in his Haystack collection. 
            <ul> <b> His paintings included: </b>
                <li> The Water Lily Pond </li>
                <li> The Flowered Garden</li>
                <li> Bouquet of Sunflowers </li>
                <li> Red Water Lilies </li>
                <li> ...and many more.</li>
            </ul>
        <h3> There is more information about Michelangelo and why he was deemed the Hero of the High Renaissance on 
            <a
                id="tribute-link"
                href="https://www.claudemonetgallery.org/biography.html"
                target="_blank"
                >National Geographic</a 
                > website.
        </h3>
        <i>As requested, using the Loren Ipsum site, I have added in text from there. "Nullam eu augue et ante dignissim rhoncus. Aenean congue velit eu mattis tincidunt. Proin sit amet nisl sapien. Nunc gravida nisl sed mattis varius. Etiam ut augue ante. Cras consectetur tincidunt ipsum sit amet sollicitudin. Proin convallis semper iaculis. Donec sit amet massa ex. Suspendisse consectetur vulputate arcu eget posuere."</i>
        </p>
    </article>

